  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Behaviors are composed of two parts: a trigger and an action sequence. A behavior’s",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "trigger defines how and when it fires, and the action sequence defines what actually",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "happens when it does. Common triggers include an object being tapped by the user,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "coming into proximity with another object in the scene, or receiving a notification",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "sent from code. Common actions include showing, hiding, and moving objects, and playing",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "sounds.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Behaviors give you a versatile way to add interactivity to a Reality Composer scene.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "To create your own new behavior, select the Custom option when adding a behavior.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The behavior is added to your scene with no defined trigger or action sequence.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Define-a-trigger",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Define a trigger",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Every behavior must contain a trigger, which defines how and when that behavior fires.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "See ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/creating-a-trigger",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Build-an-action-sequence",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Build an action sequence",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A behavior’s action sequence defines what actually happens when the behavior fires.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The sequence can consist of one or more actions that you configure to run sequentially",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or concurrently. See ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/adding-interactivity-to-behaviors",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Add-actions",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Add actions",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To add the first action to a sequence, tap or click the plus button next to the Action",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Sequence title, or in the dotted box below it, and choose one of the available actions",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "from the popover that appears. If objects in your scene are selected when you add",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "an action, the new action is automatically configured to affect the selected objects.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If no objects are selected when you create the action, specify the objects that you",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "want it to affect by using the Affected Object section at the top of the action.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Tap or click the Choose button to go into selection mode, then click or tap the object",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or objects you want the action to affect. If an object is already selected, clicking",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or tapping it removes it from being affected by the action. When you’re finished,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "press the Done button to finalize your selection.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For more information about using Reality Composer’s Actions, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/adding-interactivity-to-behaviors",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Configure-multiple-actions-to-run-concurrently",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Configure multiple actions to run concurrently",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For many behaviors, a single action is all you’ll need, but you can also create complex",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "action sequences by combining multiple actions in one sequence. By default, when",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you add another action to a sequence, it runs sequentially after the existing actions",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "finish.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Sometimes, you want two or more actions to run at the same time instead of running",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "one after the other. For example, you might want one object to flip at the same time",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that a sound plays. To make multiple actions in a sequence run concurrently, drag",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "one of the actions onto the other. The two actions’ boxes then combine into a single",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "larger box, as shown in the following figure, indicating that they now run at the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "same time. To run additional actions simultaneously, drag more actions onto the larger",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "box. To make concurrent actions sequential again, drag individual actions outside",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "of the joined box.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "building-custom-behaviors-1",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
